# Project Goals
- Make StudyHub look production-quality with clean layout, consistent spacing, and responsive design.
- Keep existing functionality (group creation/join, timer, leaderboard), but improve structure, UX, and accessibility.
- Prefer composable React components and a clear AppShell layout.

# Tech & Design
- Stack: React + Vite, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui components, lucide-react icons.
- Typography: Inter from Google Fonts. Base font-size 16px; use Tailwind scale.
- Color palette: Use Tailwind slate/neutral for base; one primary (indigo-600) with hover/active states.
- Spacing: Use 4/8/12/16/24/32 px steps (Tailwind p-1…p-8). Avoid cramped UIs.
- Components: Use Cards, Buttons, Inputs, Tabs from shadcn/ui. Avoid ad-hoc div soup.
- Accessibility: Proper semantic roles, labels, focus states, and keyboard navigation.

# Code Quality
- Enforce ESLint + Prettier; functional components; hooks only; no class components.
- Use SWR/React Query pattern if adding data fetching; keep API calls in /src/api.
- Use TypeScript types if TypeScript is enabled; if not, add JSDoc types.
- Separate layout components (/src/components/layout) from feature components (/src/features/...).

# File/Folder Conventions
/src
  /components      # Reusable UI (buttons, cards, inputs)
  /components/layout  # AppShell (Header/Sidebar/Main)
/features
  /leaderboard
  /session-timer
  /groups
/api               # Fetch wrappers
/lib               # utils, constants
/styles            # tailwind and globals

# UI Musts
- Build an AppShell: header (logo + actions), optional left sidebar (nav), main content grid.
- Leaderboard: card with table, rank medals, and subtle row hover.
- Timer: prominent, centered, accessible controls (start/pause/reset), keyboard shortcuts.
- Empty states for each feature with short helpful copy and CTA.
- Responsive: 320px→2xl; stack cards on small screens.

# Git & PR
- Use Conventional Commits: feat/ui: ..., fix: ..., refactor: ...
- Small PRs with before/after screenshots in the description.

# Don’ts
- Don’t inline giant CSS strings; prefer Tailwind utilities.
- Don’t create global mutable singletons.
- Don’t remove existing features without a migration path/testing.
